@macro localcodingstandards{}
The codebase for this course follows a coding style like the CS11 C++ track
coding style, described here:
@uref{http://courses.cms.caltech.edu/cs11/material/cpp/donnie/cppstyle.html}.
Pintos uses only spaces for indentation, @strong{no tabs}, and 4 spaces per
indentation level.  Opening curly-braces are placed on the same line as the
statement that begins the block; closing curly-braces are placed on a
separate line.
@end macro

